properties.Name: CommissionScheduleType
properties.Description:
A categorization of Commissions based on common characteristics, objectives or functions performed.

Ex:

- GOODWILL COMMISSION SCHEDULE
A Commission Schedule established to promote a special relationship with an existing customer or one that the firm wishes to establish a larger relationship with.  A Goodwill Commission Schedule contains terms that are more favorable than would normally be available to the general public.

- STANDARD COMMISSION SCHEDULE
The standard (basic or default) Commission applied to any Product transaction, which equates to the house 'standard commission'.

- NEGOTIATED COMMISSION SCHEDULE
A brokerage commission that is determined through negotiation.  Prior to 1975 commissions were fixed.    Since then brokerage firms have been free to charge whatever they want for commissions.

- PROMOTIONAL COMMISSION SCHEDULE
A special Commission Schedule that is limited in time, has specific objectives or meant to feature a specific Product, market or channel.
